A City of Tshwane health professional takes a nasal swab to test for the COVID-19 coronavirus. AFP/Phill Magakoe JOHANNESBURG - Over 8,000 new COVID-19 infections have been recorded in the past 24 hours in South Africa. This brings the cumulative total to 930,711. READ: Mkhize: New variant of COVID-19 in SA The health department said 796,346 people have recovered from the virus. Another least 216 people have died of COVID-19. The total death toll is 24,907. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.  As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 930 711, the total number of deaths is 24 907 and the total number of recoveries is 796 346. pic.twitter.com/QOgReX9SXb  #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 21 December.
